    "body": "This was not introduced in this pull but we really shouldn't be using `int` for file sizes but `off_t` for compatibility with 64 bit files (sure, if the address database is more than 2GB I'd be afraid as well... but having negative values here due to wraparound can cause bad stuff).\n",
